Paper: hep-th/0302128

Date: 2003-02-17

Title: A determination of <A^2> and the non-perturbative vacuum energy of

Yang-Mills theory in the Landau gaugeAuthors: D. Dudal, H. Verschelde, R. E. Browne, J. A. Gracey

Comments: 12 pages, 3 eps figures; v2

"suppression" correctedWe discuss the 2-point-particle-irreducible (2PPI) expansion, which sumsbubble graphs to all orders, in the context of SU(N) Yang-Mills theory in theLandau gauge. Using the method we investigate the possible existence of a gluoncondensate of mass dimension two, <A^2>, and the corresponding non-zero vacuumenergy. This condensate gives rise to a dynamically generated mass for thegluon.